```
The problem i saw two days ago maybe be caused by the unnormal status of druid cluster or too big size of mapreduce.map/reduce.memory.mb options, but i'm not sure and it does not reapper.

Thank you so much !

@leventov Thanks for the new title.

> Pruning dimensions doesn't win you anything because when querying historical data, unused dimensions are neither accessed in memory nor loaded from disk.

Pruning dimensions can reduce the number of rows. For example, there are two dimensions A and B in a segment. The cardinality of A is 10, and the cardinality of B is 100.  The max number of rows in this segment is 10*100. However, if there is only dimension A in this segment, the max number of rows in is 10.
